TITLE: Jesse Watters: Democrats are lying and hiding before this election so badly
SUMMARY: Fox News host Jesse Watters analyzes how Democrats are performing in the polls ahead of the 2022 midterm elections on "Jesse Watters Primetime."

TITLE: New York man dies after falling onto subway tracks during fight: police
SUMMARY: A 40-year-old New York City man died Monday afternoon after falling onto the subway tracks following a physical altercation with another man, police said.

TITLE: Gerrit Cole tells Yankees he can pitch if needed in do-or-die Game 5 vs. Guardians
SUMMARY: Gerrit Cole, despite throwing 110 pitches in the Yankees' win on Sunday night, reportedly told manager Aaron Boone that he can pitch if needed in Game 5 against the Guardians.

TITLE: Jerry Lee Lewis and Keith Whitley inducted into the Country Music Hall of Fame
SUMMARY: Jerry Lee Lewis and Keith Whitley got inducted into the Country Music Hall of Fame on Sunday. Garth Brooks, Kenny Chesney and Miranda Lambert performed at the ceremony.

TITLE: DeSantis' office blasts media claims that voter assistance is political: 'The distinction is clear'
SUMMARY: The governor's office responded to accusations from media pundits that the recent expansion of early voting access in hurricane-damaged counties was politically motivated.

TITLE: NYPD releases surveillance video of $500,000 jewelry heist in Manhattan
SUMMARY: Surveillance video released by the NYPD shows three suspects smashing display cases at a jewelry store in Manhattan before making off with $500,00 worth of valuables.

TITLE: Reporter's notebook: Kyiv under attack from Putin's new Iranian drones
SUMMARY: Russia launched a massive drone strike on Ukraine's capital Kyiv. The Iranian made Kamikaze drones attacked a residential building killing at least one civilian.

TITLE: Bucs' Todd Bowles 'dissatisfied with a lot of things' after loss to Steelers
SUMMARY: Todd Bowles isn't pleased with the Tampa Bay Buccaneers after falling to 3-3 following Sunday's loss to the Steelers, but he's not singling any one person out.

TITLE: Cowboys expect Dak Prescott to be cleared for practice Wednesday
SUMMARY: The Dallas Cowboys are expecting starting quarterback Dak Prescott to be cleared for practice Wednesday, setting him up to start this week against the Detroit Lions.

TITLE: Biden adding to his list of others to blame for soaring gas prices
SUMMARY: President Biden and Democrats are blaming rising gas prices on Middle Eastern countries as part of the latest effort to deflect responsibility for pain at the pump.
